n|2\n|<nowiki>- University of Mysore</nowiki>\n|-\n|History\n|2\n|<nowiki>- St Xaviers Autonomous College \u2013 Kolkata</nowiki>\n\n- Punjabi University\n|-\n|Population Studies\n|1\n|<nowiki>- Madurai Kamaraj University</nowiki>\n|-\n|Psychology\n|3\n|<nowiki>- The English & Foreign Languages University</nowiki>\n\n- IIT Madras\n|-\n|Sociology\n|1\n|<nowiki>- University of Calicut</nowiki>\n|}\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" |Language\n|-\n|English\n|5\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Literature\n|1\n|<nowiki>- The English & Foreign Languages University</nowiki>\n|-\n|Russian\n|2\n|<nowiki>- Maharaja Sayajirao University of Baroda</nowiki>\n|}\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" |Arts & Recreation\n|-\n|Audio-Visual Media\n|1\n|<nowiki>- Shiv Nadar University</nowiki>\n|-\n|Films\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Music\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Performing Arts\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Photography\n|1\n|<nowiki>- Devi Ahilya Vishwavidyalaya</nowiki>\n|-\n|Script Writing\n|1\n|<nowiki>- St Xavier\u2019s Autonomous College \u2013 Kolkata</nowiki>\n|-\n|Visual Art\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|}\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" |General\n|-\n|Research\n|1\n|<nowiki>- University of Hyderabad</nowiki>\n|}\nAnd also have post-graduate courses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/explorer|title=Swayam|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n== '''<big>Credit Transfer</big>''' ==\nAll the courses offered by SWAYAM are credible and are recognized by the government of India. All the courses are valid in the country and also, [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]] has announced a \u201cCredit Framework for Online Learning Courses through SWAYAM\u201d Regulations, 2016 in the Gazette of India on July 19, 2016 where credit transfer for SWAYAM courses is defined. The UGC regulation requires Universities to make changes in their rules and regulation to incorporate provision for credit mobility and MOOC courses under the SWAYAM platform. The certificates of degrees and diploma will be given on clearing the criteria of course taken and that certificate will be a credit mobility for academic credits<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://storage.googleapis.com/swayam1-pub-data/UGC-(Credit-Framework-for-Online-Learning-Courses-through-SWAYAM)-Regulation%2C-2016.pdf|title=Credit Framework for Online Learning Courses through SWAYAM)|date=2016-07-19|work=The Gazette of India|access-date=2020-03-29|url-status=live}}</ref>. The current guideline of UGC constrains just 20 percent of the courses for a degree-level program.\n\n== '''<big>Local Chapter</big>''' ==\n[[Nptel|NPTEL]] is a joint initiative of the [[Indian Institutes of Technology|IITs]] and [[Indian Institute of Science|IISC]], NPTEL offers online courses and certification in various fields.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nptelindia.wordpress.com/|title=NPTEL - A Joint Initiative of IITs and IISc, Bengaluru|website=NPTEL - A Joint Initiative of IITs and IISc, Bengaluru|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> NPTEL has set up a system to provide certificate courses in different colleges all over India termed as [https://nptel.ac.in/LocalChapter/about_LocalChapter.html NPTEL- local chapters]. A local chapter will be under one faculty member of the college- one single contact and so called [[Point of contact|Single Point of Contact]] (SPOC).\n\nFurther under the [https://nptel.ac.in/LocalChapter/index.html SWAYAM-NPTEL] webpage, two more departments are operated, i.e. '''[https://nptel.ac.in/LocalChapter/nptelnews.html NPTEL news]''' and '''[https://nptel.ac.in/LocalChapter/newsfromlc.html SWAYAM-NPTEL Local chapter news]'''. NPTEL news highlights bulletins about SPOC timeline, list of active local chapters, local chapter\u2019s ratings, etc. And other department shows news from local chapters i.e. local chapter colleges/universities.\n\n== '''<big>SWAYAM PRABHA</big>''' ==\n'''[https://www.swayamprabha.gov.in/ SWAYAM PRABHA]''' is an education learning platform initiated by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|the Ministry of Human Resource Development]] (MHRD) available [[24/7 service|24x7]] through 32 [[Direct-to-home television in India|DTH channels]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://swayamprabha.gov.in/|title=Swayam Prabha {{!}} Free 32 DTH channels|website=swayamprabha.gov.in|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> This initiative provide an educational program on Television on multiple time zone. The content provider is NPTEL, IITs, UGC, NCERT, etc. same as of SWAYAM online portal.\n\n<br />\n\n== '''<big>References</big>'''\u00a0\u00a0 ==\n<references />\n[[Category:Ministry of Human Resource Development (India)]]\n", "text_old": "'''[https://swayam.gov.in/ SWAYAM]''' is a Hindi acronym stands for \"'''Study Webs of Active-Learning for Young Aspiring Minds'''\" is an Indian [[Massive open online course]] (MOOC) platform. SWAYAM is an initiative launched by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|the Ministry of Human Resource Development]], [[Government of India]] under [[Digital India]] to give a coordinated stage and free entry to web courses, covering all advanced education, High School and skill sector courses.It was launched on 9th July 2017 by [[President of India|Honorable President of India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/mhrds-swayam-programme-aims-to-make-study-material-available-to-all/articleshow/67955817.cms|title=MHRD's SWAYAM programme aims to make study material available to all - Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Krishna|first=V.V.|last2=Chandra|first2=Nimesh|title=Knowledge Production and Knowledge Transfer: A Study of Two Indian Institutes of Technology (IIT Madras and IIT Bombay)|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.4337/9780857938008.00014|journal=Academic Entrepreneurship in Asia|doi=10.4337/9780857938008.00014}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/about|title=SWAYAM|date=2020-03-29|website=SWAYAM|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nSWAYAM has been developed cooperatively by MHRD (Ministry of Human Resource Development) and AICTE (All India Council for Technical Education) with the help of Microsoft and is equipped for facilitating 2,000 courses. The platform offers free access to everyone and hosts courses from class 9 till post-graduation. It enables professors and faculty of centrally funded institutes like [[Indian Institutes of Technology|IITs]], [[Indian Institutes of Management|IIMs]], [[Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research|IISERs]], etc. to teach students.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pib.gov.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=109585|title=Highlights of the Achievements of the Union HRD Ministry|website=pib.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.alkhateebgroup.org/mook.asp|title=Alkhateeb Polytechnic|website=www.alkhateebgroup.org|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> \u00a0\n\nAs per the official website, there are 203 partnering institutes, 2748 completed courses, 12541992 student enrollment, 915538 exam registrations, and 654664 successful certificates.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/|title=Details|date=2020-03-29|website=SWAYAM|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== '''<big>Functionality</big>''' ==\nSWAYAM operates MOOCs  learning resources in different ways and structure. Learning in SWAYAM has four parts/quadrants: [https://www.bristol.ac.uk/esu/media/tutorials/design-principles/page_02.htm e-Tutorial], [https://www.lexico.com/en/definition/e-content e-Content], Discussion forum, [https://www.lexico.com/en/definition/assessment Assessment].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite journal|last=Samanta|first=Anuva|date=2018-07-05|title=Analytical Study of SWAYAM|url=http://ijrar.com/upload_issue/ijrar_issue_1471.pdf|journal=Analytical Study of SWAYAM|pages=6|via=Google Scholar}}</ref>\n\nThe first quadrant is direct teaching means not much of extra work by students, it could include teaching video, [[animation]], [[Microsoft PowerPoint|PowerPoint presentation]], [[Podcast]] and so on. All these depend on what the subject is and what the strategy adopted by the teacher to teach the students.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite journal|date=2016-11-30|title=THE JOURNEY OF SWAYAM: INDIA MOOCS INITIATIVE|url=http://oasis.col.org/bitstream/handle/11599/2592/PDF?sequence=1&isAllowed=y|journal=Journey of swayam|volume=|pages=10|via=Google scholar}}</ref>\n\nThe second quadrant is an e-content which could include e-books, [https://www.lexico.com/en/definition/illustration illustrations], [[Case study|Case studies]], [[Open content|Open source content]], Reference link, further reading sources and so on.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bast|first=Dr.Felix|date=2019-07-03|title=SWAYAM MOOC education on go|url=http://nopr.niscair.res.in/bitstream/123456789/48955/1/SR%2056%287%29%2031-33.pdf|journal=education on go|volume=|pages=3|via=Google scholar}}</ref>\n\nThe third quadrant is about clearing student's queries. [[Internet forum|Discussion forum]] is a part of it means students can interact with other students and faculty to clarify their doubts. The discussion forum is like a doubt counter where any student or faculty can answer the question of a student.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nThe fourth quadrant is self-assessment to check what a student have studied and whether he/she is eligible to get certificate. It could be tests in the form of [[Multiple choice|Multiple Choice Questions]] (MCQs), or quiz or s hort answer questions, long answer questions, etc. The fourth quadrant also has Frequently Asked Question (FAQs) and their answers to clarify common misconceptions among students.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== '''<big>National Coordinators</big>''' ==\nNine national coordinators are appointed to ensure and maintain good quality content. Each coordinator has assigned a particular area for maintenance.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n1.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0[[All India Council for Technical Education]] (AICTE) has been appointed National coordinator by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]] for self-paced and international courses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/AICTE|title=Swayam Central|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> \n\n2.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0[[Nptel|National Programme on Technology Enhanced Learning]] (NPTEL) has been appointed National coordinator by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]] for engineering sector courses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/NPTEL|title=Swayam Central|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n3.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0[[University Grants Commission (India)|University Grants Permission]] (UGC) has been appointed National coordinator by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]] for non-technical post-graduate education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/UGC|title=Swayam Central|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n4.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0[http://cec.nic.in/cec/ Consortium for Educational Communication] (CEC) has been appointed National coordinator by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]] for undergraduate education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/CEC|title=Swayam Central|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n5.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0[[National Council of Educational Research and Training]] (NCERT) has been appointed National coordinator by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]] for school education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/NCERT|title=Swayam Central|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n6.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0[[National Institute of Open Schooling]] (NIOS) has been appointed National coordinator by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]] for school education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/NIOS|title=Swayam Central|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n7.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0[[National Institute of Open Schooling|Indira Gandhi National Open University]] (IGNOU) has been appointed National coordinator by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]] for out-of-school students.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/IGNOU|title=Swayam Central|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n8.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0[[Indian Institute of Management Bangalore|Indian Institute of Management, Bangalore]] (IIMB) has been appointed National coordinator by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]] for management studies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/IIMB|title=Swayam Central|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n9.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0[[Indian Institute of Management Bangalore|National Institute of Technical Teachers Training and Research]] (NITTTR) has been appointed National coordinator by [[Ministry of Human Resource Development|MHRD]] for Teacher training program.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://swayam.gov.in/nc_details/NITTTR|title=Swayam Central|website=swayam.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n<br />\n\n== <big>'''Courses offered'''</big> ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|Subject\n|No. of courses\n|Offered by/under\n|}\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" |SCHOOL\n|-\n|Accountary\n|1\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Biology\n|3\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Business studies\n|1\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Chemistry\n|3\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Economics\n|2\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Food Nutrition for Healthy Living\n|1\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Geography\n|2\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Mathematics\n|3\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Physics\n|4\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Psychology\n|2\n|NCERT\n|-\n|Sociology\n|2\n|NCERT\n|}\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" |Undergraduate courses\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" |Engineering\n|-\n|Aerospace\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Bioengineering\n|3\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Biotechnology\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Chemical\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Civil\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|\n\n\n\n\nComputer Science\n|18\n|<nowiki>- Punjabi University</nowiki>\n\n- Panjab University\n\n- Anna University\n\n- Gujarat University\n\n- IIT Madras\n\n- IGNOU\n|-\n|Electrical\n|4\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nElectronics\n|115\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n\n- Anna University\n\n- IIT Mumbai\n\n- IIT Kanpur\n\n- IIT Roorkee\n\n- IIT Kharagpur\n\n- IISc\n\n- IIT Delhi\n\n- IIT Guwahati\n\n- IISER Kolkata\n\n- IIIT Delhi\n|-\n|Environment\n|1\n|<nowiki>- Devi Ahilya Vishwavidyalaya</nowiki>\n|-\n|\n\n\n\nGeneral\n|31\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n\n- IIT Kanpur\n\n- IIT Roorkee\n\n- IIT Kharagpur\n\n- IIT Mumbai\n|-\n|Geology\n|1\n|<nowiki>- Dr. Harisingh Gour Vishwavidyalaya</nowiki>\n|-\n|Graphics\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Instrumentation-and-Control\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Mechanical\n|8\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Metallurgy\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|}\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" |Management\n|-\n|Entrepreneurship\n|2\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Finance\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Human Resources\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|\n\n\nMarketing\n|3\n|<nowiki>- Jai Narain Vyas University</nowiki>\n\n- SP Pune University\n\n- IIT Madras\n|-\n|Operations Research\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Services\n|2\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n\n- IIM Bangalore\n|}\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" |Science\n|-\n|Biochemistry\n|1\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</nowiki>\n|-\n|Biology\n|1\n|<nowiki>- Gujarat University</nowiki>\n|-\n|\n\n\n\nChemistry\n|5\n|<nowiki>- IGNOU</nowiki>\n\n- IIT Roorkee\n\n- University of Delhi\n\n- IIT Madras\n|-\n|Genetics\n|1\n|<nowiki>- University of Kashmir</nowiki>\n|-\n|Physics\n|2\n|<nowiki>- IIT Madras</