h Parry Sound:\n\n* [[Marty Adams]], actor, writer and comedian\n* [[Samuel Armstrong (Canadian politician)|Samuel Armstrong]] (1844\u20131921), businessman and politician<ref>https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.1.1/JD68-K8L {{subscription required}}</ref>\n* [[James Arthurs]] (1866\u20131937), politician and senator<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=qYwjAAAAIBAJ&pg=6557%2C967100 | title=Senator J. Arthurs Dies in 72nd Year | newspaper=[[The Gazette (Montreal)|The Gazette]] | author=[[The Canadian Press]] | location=Montreal | date=8 October 1937 | accessdate=2010-04-02 }}</ref> \n* [[Bill Beagan]] (born 1937), National Hockey League referee and commissioner of four hockey leagues<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bobbyorrhalloffame.com/inductee/bill-beagan/|title=Bill Beagan|website=Bobby Orr Hall of Fame|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[William Rabb Beatty]] (1851\u20131905), businessman and politician<ref>https://www.ola.org/en/members/all/874</ref>\n* [[Neil Belland]] (born 1961), professional ice hockey player<ref>http://www.hockeydb.com/ihdb/stats/pdisplay.php?pid=7445</ref>\n* [[Fred Bourdginon]] (1906-1995), professional ice hockey player<ref>http://www.hockeydb.com/ihdb/stats/pdisplay.php?pid=29870</ref> \n* [[John Brackenborough]] (1897\u20131993), professional ice hockey player \n* [[Gerald Carson]] (1903\u20131956), professional ice hockey player<ref>http://www.hockeydb.com/ihdb/stats/pdisplay.php?pid=844</ref> \n* [[Wayne Clairmont]] (born 1943), professional ice hockey player<ref>http://www.hockeydb.com/ihdb/stats/pdisplay.php?pid=10281</ref>\n* [[Terry Crisp]] (born 1943), professional ice hockey player and coach<ref>https://www.hhof.com/LegendsOfHockey/jsp/SearchPlayer.jsp?player=12370</ref>\n* [[Eleanor Joanne Daley]] (born 1955), composer and choir director<ref>http://www.alliancemusic.com/peopledetails.cfm?iPeopleID=4</ref>\n* [[Douglas Durkin]]\n* [[Ernie Eves]]\n* [[Donald Guloien]]\n* [[Mark Ideson]]\n* [[Allan Loney]]\n* [[William Morgan (judoka)|William Morgan]]\n* [[Bobby Orr]]<ref name=\"Orr\" />\n* [[Gary Sabourin]]\n* [[James Sharpe (Canadian politician)|James Sharpe]]\n* [[Fred J. Stevenson]]\n* [[William Sutherland (Ontario politician)|William Sutherland]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Parry Sound, Ontario}}\n*{{wikivoyage-inline|Parry Sound}}\n*[http://www.parrysound.ca/ Town of Parry Sound]\n\n{{Geographic location\n | Centre    = Parry Sound\n | North     = [[McDougall, Ontario|McDougall]]\n | Northeast = \n | East      = [[McDougall, Ontario|McDougall]]\n | Southeast = \n | South     = [[Seguin, Ontario|Seguin]]\n | Southwest = [[Wasauksing First Nation]]\n | West      = ''[[Parry Sound]]''\n | Northwest = \n}}\n{{Parry Sound District}}\n\n[[Category:Parry Sound, Ontario| ]]\n[[Category:Populated places on Lake Huron in Canada]]\n[[Category:Single-tier municipalities in Ontario]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the town|the body of water in Georgian Bay, Ontario|Parry Sound}}\n<!-- Infobox begins -->\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Parry Sound\n| official_name                   = Town of Parry Sound\n| settlement_type                 = [[List of towns in Ontario|Town]] ([[List of municipalities in Ontario#Single-tier municipalities|single-tier]])\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name                     = <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n| nickname                        = \n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = Aerial view of Parry Sound.jpg\n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = Looking over the town and the sound\n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_shield                    = \n| shield_size                     = \n| image_blank_emblem              = \n| blank_emblem_